</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Some time ago, an acquaintance took out a Small Business Development Loan.
When he came to clear this, his accountant estimated he still owed some
Pounds 9,000 interest. But the bank involved claimed that, because the 'Rule
of Three' applied, he owed more than Pounds 30,000 interest. Just what is
