<HEADLINE>
FT  07 MAY 94 / Finance and the Family: Directors' transactions
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By VIVIEN MACDONALD, The Inside Track
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The Capita Group is involved in various aspects of management consultancy.
Its recent final results showed some improvement in pre-tax profit and
chairman Rodney Aldridge made a broadly optimistic statement.
He and chief executive Paul Pindar (who combines the roles of managing and
finance director), plus Richard Benton and John Brameld all sold stock on
Friday April 29 at 223p.
Directors of Capita Group sell stock regularly at this time of year, but the
steady rise in the share price has meant that they have raised more money
this time than ever before.
Secure Retirement is a newcomer to the market. The company develops
sheltered housing - one of the sectors to gain more and more prominence in
recent years in light of the increasing longevity of the UK population.
Following an introduction to the market, all the directors have been dealing
apace, dipping repeatedly into the market. While the overall value of the
transactions is not enormous when divided by the number of those dealing,
the enthusiasm is certainly great.
Virtuality also is a recent arrival on the market. In its case, however, the
flotation has allowed managing director Dr Jonathan Waldren and chairman
David Payne to realise some cash by selling a proportion of their holdings.
