<HEADLINE>
FT  06 MAY 94 / UK Company News: Acquisitions behind 64% increase at Forward
Group
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL CHEESERIGHT, Midlands Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Forward Group, the specialist circuit board and chemicals manufacturer,
raised annual profits by 64 per cent, helped by the first contribution from
Central Circuits, a Telford-based company purchased from the receiver in
February 1993.
Over the 12 months to January 31, pre-tax profits improved from Pounds 1.23m
to Pounds 2.02m. Acquisitions contributed Pounds 5.6m to turnover which
jumped to Pounds 20.7m (Pounds 12.5m), and Pounds 595,000 to operating
profits of Pounds 2.23m (Pounds 1.44m).
The purchase of Central Circuits widened Forward's manufacturing base,
although it has temporarily taken the group closer to the mass market for
circuit boards and diluted turnover of its usual specialist low volume, high
value business.
Looking at the group's main markets, Mr Ray Chamberlain, chairman, said
there had been some improvement in the electronics industry, but that
telecommunications was more of a growth area than military business. The
group's business with medical customers was also growing.
Earnings per share rose from 11.06p to 16.71p. The proposed final dividend
is 3p, bringing the total to 5p (3.3p).
