<HEADLINE>
FT  06 MAY 94 / DTI closes tour operator
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RAYMOND SNODDY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The Department of Trade and Industry yesterday closed WorldWide Theme
Travel, a tour operator that traded as WTT Flights and Leisure.
The company, based in the City of London, was expelled from the Association
of British Travel Agents last year. It specialised in travel to Spain,
Portugal and Malta. Customers now abroad will be able to continue their
holidays and passengers planning to fly abroad after midnight tomorrow will
be given refunds, the Civil Aviation Authority said.
Mr Keith Betton, Abta's head of corporate affairs, said it had received
hundreds of complaints from customers alleging irregular withdrawals from
credit cards, refunds which never arrived and pressure selling.
'They were a company that brought our industry and our association into
disrepute and we were not prepared for them to remain in membership any
longer,' he said.
